</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#F5F5DC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/udaelluclin.showPublicProfile?language=EN>dael luclin</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 36<br> <font color=#FF0000>(3/23/01 6:50:30 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub6.ezboard.com/fluclin71335dragonsandtheplanes.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=673.topic&index=9>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Time to share Plane of Hate!</span><hr size=1> not reasonable unless a way to get to 2nd floor without clearing any of the old mobs existed.  3 of the new boss mobs spawn on the 2nd floor in the old inny chamber which is a guaranteed 6 armor drops (or god drops) plus all the roamers in that area.  The only safe place to CoH a group to get in there would be id imagine the base of the ramp leading to second floor but fighting the 2 drakes that are on top of the ramp would be very very dangerous outside of a fully spawned maestro hall.  The only reasonable way to do this would be if the 2 groups worked in conjunction, with one group pulling from zone in to the ramps and then clearing the old mobs on 2nd floor then told the other guild they had done that and the other guild then moved up and past the old area into the new area.<br>
seems to me it would be a very tedious process, either one group (new area group will be higher level) fights through and takes a lot of armor drops from the other group, or the upstairs group waits til the downstairs group is done...big pain in the ass imho <p>Dael Stormseeker<br>
