Loyal to the House of Fortitude<br>
~APEX~</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#CCCCCC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/uheimdol.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Heimdol</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://members.aol.com/scubalinx/dflag.gif BORDER=0 WIDTH=10 HEIGHT=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 61<br> <font color=#FF0000>(3/28/01 11:45:45 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub6.ezboard.com/fluclin71335dragonsandtheplanes.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=673.topic&index=10>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Time to share Plane of Hate!</span><hr size=1> I don't think we are at a point where this is a need on this server.  There are still many open days each week to go hunt for armor.  There is no need to crowd out other raids to do it.  I could understand if this was the Rathe Server but not here.  Not to mention the obvious points others have made.  It would be almost impossible to take the second floor without killing the first floor of Maestro's hall and then there is the matter of getting folks to Maestro's hall in the first place without killing a bunch of the first level stuff to do it.  I just don't think its practical for us to do it at this point on our server.  There just isn't a need for it yet. <p><img src="http://members.aol.com/scubalnks/cscicon22.gif"><FONT face="arial,helvetica" size="2" color="#000000">Heimdol Thunderspirit - 55 Barbarian/Shaman</FONT>
